main event: Five yellow/white objects were observed moving across the sky in Philadelphia, PA for less than a minute.
interesting points: The first two objects seemed to travel north and northwest after appearing in the east.
The third object appeared in the north traveling south, while the remaining two were observed in the east, traveling east.
No visual aids were used by the observer.
The observer position that the objects were not northeast.
The observer's descriptions of the objects suggested they were similar to missiles, and the sighting was attributed to a meteorological shower.
